TAMPA — Police were investigating after a man was found mortally injured outside a 7-11 store early Friday. Police received a 911 call around 1:20 a.m. about an altercation outside the store at 4943 E Busch Blvd. When officers arrived, they found an unconscious man in the parking lot who was suffering from “severe upper body trauma,” police said. The man was taken to a local hospital and died there a short time later, according to police. Police have not released the man’s name or any other details. Detectives continued to investigate Friday. This is a developing story. Check tampabay.com for updates.